 :tx/rationale "GENESIS-4: EMBEDDING INFRASTRUCTURE via frankensearch/model2vec. Semantic embeddings preserve the LLM's associative structure — two observations about the same subsystem have nearby embeddings even with zero keyword overlap. The enabling technology: model2vec/potion-128M (256-dim, safetensors, no API calls, ~0.5ms per embedding, deterministic output). This is a static embedder — vocabulary lookup + mean-pool, not a neural network forward pass. From safetensors file, fully offline, C8-compatible. frankensearch already packages this: two-tier embedding (fast: potion-128M 256-dim, quality: MiniLM-L6-v2 384-dim), FSVI vector storage, BM25+vector hybrid search via Reciprocal Rank Fusion. For braid: at observe time, compute 256-dim embedding of observation text, store as :exploration/embedding Bytes datom. Connection scoring becomes cosine similarity on embeddings — O(concepts) per observation. For concept centroids: running mean of member embeddings. For concept matching: cosine(observation_embedding, concept_centroid) > JOIN_THRESHOLD. This replaces Jaccard as the PRIMARY connection signal. Jaccard remains as fallback when embeddings unavailable. Dependency: frankensearch crate or model2vec directly. ~5MB binary size increase (safetensors model file). No API calls. No network. Deterministic."
